<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-09T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-09T17:00:00-05:00" n="114" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d114">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Pacific War/876:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Erwin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-09T16:00:00-06:00">December 9, 1941—4 p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 8:29
                                    p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>114. The Honduran Foreign Minister requests me to convey a message
                                from the President of Honduras tendering to the United States <pb facs="0108" n="98" xml:id="pg_98"/> Government any facilities on
                                the Atlantic coast as well as Fonseca Bay and also the use of these
                                waters for naval bases or any other purposes.</p>
                            <p>The Honduran Government is communicating with the Governments of
                                Nicaragua and El Salvador requesting them to collaborate in this
                                matter.</p>
                            <p>Repeated to Managua, San Salvador and Naval Attaché.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Erwin</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>